methods.description: Bitwise right rotate.  Normally this will compile to a singleinstruction, especially if the shift is a manifest constant.

methods.name: hashLen17to32
methods.description: This probably works well for 16-byte strings as well, but it may be overkillin that case.

methods.name: weakHashLen32WithSeeds0
methods.description: Return a 16-byte hash for 48 bytes.  Quick and dirty.Callers do best to use "random-looking" values for a and b.

methods.name: weakHashLen32WithSeeds1
methods.description: Return a 16-byte hash for s[0] ... s[31], a, and b.  Quick and dirty.

methods.name: hashLen33to64
methods.description: Return an 8-byte hash for 33 to 64 bytes.

methods.name: cityHash64
methods.description: Hash function for a byte array.

methods.name: cityHash64WithSeed
methods.description: Hash function for a byte array.  For convenience, a 64-bit seed is alsohashed into the result.

methods.name: cityHash32
methods.description: Hash function for a byte array.  Most useful in 32-bit binaries.

methods.name: cityHash128to64
methods.description: Hash 128 input bits down to 64 bits of output.This is intended to be a reasonably good hash function.
